  dialogueSteps:
  - line: "The light has just turned orange \u2014 can we continue now?"
    stepType: 1
    correctOptionIndex: 2
    feedbackCorrect: "Correct. Orange means prepare to stop \u2014 you should only
      go if it\u2019s unsafe to stop safely. This keeps you and others safe."
    feedbackWrong: Not quite. Orange means slow down and prepare to stop. Going through
      an orange light can be dangerous.
    buttonTexts:
    - Yes, continue
    - Yes, just be careful, pedestrians still have right of way
    - No, stop and wait
    - Only if no pedestrians are crossing
